    "43834463": {
      "title": "Innate lymphoid cells promote lung-tissue homeostasis after infection with influenza virus",
      "abstract": "Cytokine-producing innate lymphoid cells are found at mucosal surfaces. Artis and Wherry and their colleagues show that innate 'nuocyte-like' cells accumulate in virus-infected lungs and contribute to the repair of tissues."
